Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
timing_hierarc...clock_mismatch(25.10)  timing_hierarc...clock_mismatch(25.10)

Name
       timing_hierarchical_context_continue_on_top_block_clock_mismatch

Syntax
       timing_hierarchical_context_continue_on_top_block_clock_mismatch

       {true | false}

       Default: false

       Allows loading of the timing context model with unmapped clocks.

       When  set  to  true,  the software allows the script to process even if
       there are any mismatches between the top and  block-level  clocks.  The
       mismatches  are  reported  in the timing_context_clock_mapping_data.rpt
       file, which shows data that allows you to determine if  corrections  or
       additions are required to the clock mapping file.

       When  set to false, the software will show an error condition if any of
       the top-level clocks cannot be matched with a block-level clock.

       To set this global variable, use the set command.

